''Acts 20:27''

The whole counsel of god or the whole of God's revelation includes all God's truths, commandments...

<<<
The secret things belong to the LORD our God, but the things that are revealed belong to us and to our children forever, that we may do all the words of this law.
<<<
''Deuteronomy 29:29''

The things that are revealed belong to us forever. Last time we discussed about divine revelation. Everything that we have known about God belongs to us because He had revealed to us.

General vs Natural revelation

What does it bring up in us when we see God's creation? Psalm 18

We study the attributes of God not simply to know about God but to know God personally and intimately. This is a relationship that we can have forever. As we consider the attributes of God, that is what we want to consider. By looking at God, we will be drawn to our knees in worship. That we will adore and worship Him.

The Hebrew word for "revealed" speaks of to uncover ourselves and show. God is saying that He is showing Himself to us. Saying in such a way that this is the most important thing that we should pass this down to our children.

When we die, what is it that we want to pass down? What is the most important to me? That is my relationship to Jesus Christ. My knowledge of God and understanding of Him is the strongest thing in which we can give to Him.

If we were to leave this Earth and not pass this on to our children, would this not be an issue.

Recently how many churches nowadays and properties are now taking something else. Might it be that our faiths have been reduced to works or a certain way of living. Our faith has been reduced to something that is not internally and eternal.

That, of course, will not last forever. As we look at the attributes of the Lord, our goal is to understand fully what it means to know God.

Attribute:  a quality or feature regarded as a characteristic or inherent part i.e. His traits.

