<<<
Then Moses said to God, "If I come to the people of Israel and say to them, 'The God of your fathers has sent me to you,' and they ask me, 'What is his name?' what shall I say to them?" God said to Moses, "I AM WHO I AM." And he said, "Say this to the people of Israel: 'I AM has sent me to you.'" [...]
<<<
''Exodus 3:13-15''

The Word "I AM" means to be. He doesn't say I was or will be. This speaks of His eternality. Immutable and unchanging. He always have and always is.

<<<
God also said to Moses, "Say this to the people of Israel, 'The LORD, the God of your fathers, the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob, has sent me to you. 'This is my name forever, and thus I am to be remembered throughout all generations.
<<<
''Exodus 3:15''

"I AM" is God's name forever. In the Hebrew tradition, the name communicates attributes about the person. Jacob's means sur-planter. Esau's name means hairy one.

Attributes of God per His name:
Self-Existent, Immutable and Eternal

We will be looking at the other attributes. We will be looking at other attributes like His holiness. When we look at the attributes of God, we are looking at Jesus. When we think of Jesus and Holiness, we think of God's wrath and those who are unholy.

